  "title": "Business Development Executive (Pharmaceutical, Healthcare)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Market and distribute a variety of orthopaedic implant systems to surgeons and healthcare institutions</li><li>Offer clinical assistance and support during surgical procedures, ensuring proper use of products</li><li>Manage product-related activities and inventory at designated hospitals</li><li>Coordinate the preparation and delivery of implants and surgical instrument sets needed for operations</li><li>Work closely with the sales team by participating in continuous learning, skill development, and knowledge exchange</li><li>Collect insights on competitors and stay updated on market trends, customer needs, and industry developments</li><li>Comprehensive training will be provided to help you succeed and grow within the role</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Nursing, Life Sciences, Biomedical Science, or a related field</li><li>Experience in medical device sales, surgical support or orthopedic</li><li>Excellent communication, negotiation and presentation skills</li></ul><p>Interested applicants for the above advertised position(s), please kindly email an updated copy of your resume to: <strong>gs1@talenttradersg.com;</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>EA License No.: 13C6305</p><p>Registration No.: R23117856 CHOE KIN MUN</p><p><br /></p><p>For candidate who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p>",
